Governor Ayodele Fayose has stated that First Lady Aisha Buhari is “as guilty as he is of corrupt charges.”
The governor stated this in a recent interview with FRESH 105.9FM in Ibadan, Oyo state.
He said: “Aisha Buhari is as guilty as me on corruption charges.
“Nobody can win any battle against me.”
ALSO SEE: Aisha Buhari sues Fayose, media aides

Governor Ayodele Fayose further described the current government led by President Muhammadu Buhari as ‘one chance.,’ stressing that the APC has failed the Nigerian people.

He said “APC is a government of ‘one chance’. Everything I’ve predicted would happen in Nigeria are happening, some have happened.

“Buhari can’t take Nigeria out of the woods. Food security is better than general security, hence my ‘stomach Infrastructure’ policy.

“Ekiti will be in economic bondage until 2036 because of debts collected by former Governor Kayode Fayemi, so my hands are tied”.


			
